videoSnippet.title: Sacrificing the Queen Just For Fun :)
videoSnippet.description:
You are awesome! :)

Anish Giri vs thesimpsonsnerd42
Optiver Warwick Winners simul
Lichess, 3.9.2021.
Ruy Lopez, closed defence (C84)

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. d3 { C84 Ruy Lopez: Closed, Martinez Variation } b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. a3 O-O 9. Nc3 Bg4 10. Be3 Nd4 11. Bxd4 exd4 12. Nd5 c6 13. Nf4?! { (0.86 → 0.28) Inaccuracy. h3 was best. } (13. h3) 13... Nh5?! { (0.28 → 0.82) Inaccuracy. d5 was best. } (13... d5 14. h3) 14. h3 Nxf4?! { (0.68 → 1.40) Inaccuracy. Bxf3 was best. } (14... Bxf3) 15. hxg4 c5 16. g3 Ng6 17. Kg2 Qd7 18. Nh2 Rac8 19. Bd5 Rfe8?! { (1.03 → 1.61) Inaccuracy. Bd8 was best. } (19... Bd8) 20. Rh1 Bf8? { (1.35 → 2.66) Mistake. Bd8 was best. } (20... Bd8) 21. g5 Ne7 22. Qh5? { (2.56 → 1.38) Mistake. Ba2 was best. } (22. Ba2 c4 23. Qh5 Qe6 24. Ng4 Qg6 25. Qh3 Rc5 26. f4 cxd3 27. cxd3 Rc2+ 28. Kg1 h6) 22... g6?? { (1.38 → 6.53) Blunder. Nxd5 was best. } (22... Nxd5 23. Ng4 h6 24. exd5 Qe7 25. gxh6 g6 26. Qh4 Qxh4 27. Rxh4 Be7 28. Rhh1 Kh7 29. a4) 23. Qxh7+ Kxh7 24. Ng4+ Kg7?? { (6.25 → Mate in 3) Checkmate is now unavoidable. Bh6 was best. } (24... Bh6 25. Nf6+ Kg7 26. Rxh6 Nxd5 27. Rh7+ Kf8 28. Nxd7+ Ke7 29. exd5 Kxd7 30. Rxf7+ Re7 31. Rf6) 25. Nf6 Qh3+ 26. Rxh3 Nf5 27. Rh7# { White wins by checkmate. } 1-0
